defaultAbout EDF Energy
default&#xa0;defaultEDF Energy is one of the UK’s largest energy companies with activities throughout the energy chain. 
default 
defaultWe provide 50% of the UK
default’s low carbon generation. 
default 
defaultOur interests include nuclear, coal and gas-fired electricity generation, renewables, and energy supply to end users. 
default 
defaultWe have over five million electricity and gas customer accounts in the UK, including both residential and 
defaultbusiness users.
default&#xa0;
defaultEDF Energy’s safe and secure operation of its eight existing nuclear power stations at sites across the country makes it the UK’s largest generator of low carbon electricity. 
default 
defaultEDF Energy is also leading the UK's nuclear renaissance and has
default published plans to build four new nuclear plants, subject to the right investment framework. 
default 
defaultThese new plants could generate enough low carbon electricity for about 40% of Britain’s homes.
default&#xa0;
defaultEDF Energy is part of EDF Group, one of Europe’s largest power c
defaultompanies. 
default 
defaultThe company employs around 15,000 people at locations across the UK.
