default19.
default              
defaultIt is essential that all students are provided with quality careers guidance from ages 14 – 18, when the choices of A-Level and degree subjects are made. 
default 
defaultThis careers guidance must come from both educational institutions and employers in the engineering s
defaultector. 
default 
defaultGovernmental policy and practice that supports the provision of this careers guidance is essential.  
default&#xa0;
default20.
default              
defaultThe creation of female role models in Engineering is also of critical importance.  The understanding of, and engagement in, their field of sc
defaultience has improved significantly in recent years, largely due to the popularisation of role models such as Prof Brian Cox through national media.  There is less understanding and awareness of engineers and engineering careers, and therefore nation-wide pro
defaultmotion of key female role models in this field would significantly help develop interest in careers in the Engineering field.
default&#xa0;
default21.
default              
defaultThe development of local role models is supported largely by the STEM Ambassador programme of schools intervention.
default 
default STEM Ambassadors significantly improve the accessibility of STEM professions to students of all ages, and increase awareness of the variety of careers and 
defaultopportunities available to engineers or all backgrounds.  It is of critical importance that this pro
defaultgramme continues to be supported and grown within the UK.
default&#xa0;defaultConclusion
default&#xa0;
default22.
default              
defaultEDF Energy is making progress in working to widen actively the pool of talent from which we recruit. 
default 
defaultWhile we have seen progress in increasing the number of female entrants to our 
defaultSTEM areas (such as the nuclear science and engineering graduate scheme and apprentice scheme), we recognise that there is more still that we, as a company, and as an industry, can do.
default&#xa0;
default13.
default              
defaultWe would highlight the significant of using positive role models t
defaulto attract women into STEM careers, and how targeted marketing STEM opportunities (both through role models and also through using specific recruitment channels such as at targeted university events) has increased the number of applications from women.
default 
default We 
defaultmust always recruit the best person for the role, however
default,
default widening our pool enables high-potential females to join an industry they may not have previously considered. 
default&#xa0;
default24.
default              
defaultIt is important for Government and industry to work together to increase the enga
defaultgement of female students at all academic stages of their STEM careers. 
default 
defaultThe promotion of STEM through female role models, sound career advice, and increasing the visibility of the engineering sector as a career prospect for women will he
defaultlp us achieve our 
defaultcommon goals.
